  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a hot-pot-vessel over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onions and minced garlic to sauté for about 5 minutes.",
    "Gently add Bramley apples, cover with thyme and bay leaves, and cook for another 10-12 minutes or until the apples are soft but not mushy.",
    "Stir in lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Continue cooking for an additional 2-3 minutes to allow flavors to meld together.",
    "Serve hot as a comforting dish over steamed rice or on its own."
